@node Installation " Program Installation"

 @{b}@{u}Installation@{uu}@{ub}

 Just use the installation script.
 If you want to use lexicon from AmIRC make an alias

 /alias lex /rx Rexx/Vent.AMIRX PATH:lex %p
 (default path = c:) 
 and then save your AmIRC configuration 
(where is PATH: insert the  path you installed lexicon)
 
@endnode


@node intro "Introduction"

@{b}@{u}Introduction@{uu}@{ub}

This is a multi dictionary (lexicon in greek). It supports
english to greek (&vice versa) and italian to greek (&vice versa)
It can be used from cli, gui or from AmIRC. 

Datafiles that contains in this version:

english to greek = 12270 words into dir lexdatabase/English/#?.dte
greek to english = 11742 words into dir lexdatabase/English/#?.dtg
italian to greek = 7528  words into dir lexdatabase/Italian/#?.dte
greek to italian = 9673  words into dir lexdatabase/Italian/#?.dtg

@endnode

@node Usage "Usage"

 @{b}@{u}Usage@{uu}@{ub}

type lex ?

Usage: lex <option> [word]
                     Options:
 without an option             -g  translates from 
 translates from                   greek to english
 english to greek

 -i translates from           -gi translates from      
     italian to greek              greek to italian



 lex englishWord
outputs the greek translation 
 
 lex -g greekword
outputs the english translation

if you want to add a word to your lexdatabase just type:

lex -a englishWord greekWord         <--- adds english and greek

lex -addit italianWord greekWord     <--- adds italian and greek

...and will add it in both english (or italian) <.dte> and greek <.dtg> datafiles
        

@endnode

@node letters "Letter correspondance"

character correspondance of greek to latin:

α=a alfa            ν=n  ni
β=b beta            ξ=3  ksi
γ=g gamma           ο=o  omikron
δ=d delta           π=p  pi
ε=e epsilon         ρ=r  ro
ζ=z zeta            σ=s  sigma
η=h eta             τ=t  tau
θ=8 theta           υ=y  ypsilon
ι=i iota            φ=f  fi
κ=k kappa           χ=x  chi
λ=l lamda           ψ=ps psi
μ=m mi              ω=w  omega

this is not the excact correspondance, its the most common way
to write with latin caracters on IRC ;-) , it's called greecklish 
@endnode

@node create "Creating your own datafiles"

You can make your own datafiles for any language Just copy them in the 
directories language1 and language2 with always the extension .dte & .dtg

@{b}EXAMBLE@{ub} how to create your datafiles:
Let's suppose you wan't to create an english to italian and a italian to english
Just make a file named a.dte and write with a text editor the words in a format like..

"ALL"."tutti"

...and so on...
copy it to the language1 directory. Then create another file a.dtg (warning .dtg 
@{b}NOT?@{ub} .dte) and write

"ANNO"."year"

...and so on... and copy it to the language2 directory.

see the current files for examble in the dir LeXiCoN/lexdatabase/

@endnode


